          About this item

          • 8-core AMD Ryzen 7 6800H Dominating battlefields with 16 threads and 16MB L3 cache, this processor offers efficient multitasking while the updated thermals maintain optimal performance.

          • Popular games Enjoy a wide variety of games like Counterstrike, Call of Duty, GTA V, Cyberpunk 2077, World of Warcraft, Minecraft, The Witcher 3, God of War 4, FIFA 23, Gotham Knights, and more.

          • Long-lasting battery With an impressive 6-cell, 83 Wh battery, game for longer without needing to recharge. Fast charge your device up to 50% in 30 minutes.
          • High-speed connectivity Equipped with Wi-Fi 6E and Bluetooth 5.3 for better connectivity. The laptop also includes ports such as 2 x USB Type-C, 3 x USB Type-A, and 1 x HDMI 2.1, and 1 x RJ-45.

              5.0 out of 5 stars It's legit
              Reviewed in India on 13 May 2023
              Verified Purchase
              The price is definitely suspicious, but I got it last week and can confirm that it's legitimate. It's brand new, not refurbished. I didn't find a single scratch or fingerprint on it when I took it out of the box. Since this is a new model that was not available before, refurbished pieces probably don't even exist.

              I ran benchmarks for both the CPU and the GPU, and they are in line with what you'd expect for this combination (R7 6800H + RTX 3070ti). Did not observe any throttling after long hours of gaming, but that's not to say that it doesn't get hot. Still, the heat is not felt on the keyboard and it won't singe your palms.

              The screen looks great, and it is QHD as advertised. It does wobble like some others have mentioned, but I personally don't find that to be a serious problem. This is the sort of laptop that you'd keep on a desk all the time and the screen does not wobble when you play or type on the keyboard.

              The audio is okay, hardly any bass at all.

              All in all, it's a real bargain if you get it for less than 120k.
